   \partial_a \int_{-\infty}^\infty  N(a+x) n(x) \mathrm{d} x = \int_{-\infty}^\infty  n(a+x) n(x) \mathrm{d} x = \int_{-\infty}^\infty  n(-a-x) n(x) \mathrm{d} x = n\left(-\frac{a}{\sqrt{2}} \right)\frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} 
