    \int_{-\infty}^\infty  N(a+x) n(x) \mathrm{d} x = \int_{-\infty}^a n\left(-\frac{b}{\sqrt{2}} \right) \frac{1}{\sqrt{2}} \mathrm{d} b = 1 - N\left(-\frac{a}{\sqrt{2}} \right) = N\left(\frac{a}{\sqrt{2}} \right) 
